caption: Last home of the famous rock n roll singer from the Doors who died here in 1971.
I was totally blown away to think this was the last apartment and place Jim Morrison lived and was before he sadly died. RIP Jim

There’s a nice likeness on the door, but also a sign in English saying that Jim Morrison did not die here…perhaps to discourage the hordes who have also made the trek to Père Lachaise cemetery over the years. (Or maybe because he lived here, but actually died at a club on the left bank…)
Cool to see, but sad at the same time

This is where Jim and Pam stayed. Contrary to the Pam’s version of events, Jim didn’t die in this apartment. He died in Rock’n’Roll Circus. The restaurant across the street used to have a memorial to Morrison, with various objects from the apartment.
A small graffiti and a music box that doesn't work anymore. Shame. You could add grafitis and information about his life
Piece of rock-history. Beautiful building altogether.
No more any indication about this place
Nice but there is only one door. I was expecting the doors.
